    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Barrier posts, generally permanent and of a sturdy material such as stone, concrete, or metal, placed between the street and the pedestrian sidewalk, or at another place intended to prevent passage The posts are generally waist high or lower; and may be joined by chains or cords.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
